    <!-- Help Dialog Content -->
    <string name="help_local_title">100% Local &amp; Private</string>
    <string name="help_local_desc">Your data belongs to you. PlacesTracker stores all experiences, images, and GPS data exclusively locally on your device. There is no communication with a server, and no personal data is uploaded to the cloud.</string>

    <string name="help_types_title">Experience vs. Trip</string>
    <string name="help_types_desc">An experience is a single point on the map, e.g., a nice restaurant or a view. A trip, on the other hand, is an entire journey with multiple stops. During an active trip, the app records \"Mini-Stops\" (waypoints) in the background so you can precisely retrace your route later.</string>

    <string name="help_auto_trip_title">Auto Trip</string>
    <string name="help_auto_trip_desc">Don\'t want to create every stop manually? Use the automatic feature! Simply select multiple images from your gallery. A smart algorithm analyzes the shooting locations and times, bundles images at the same locations into stops, and creates a finished itinerary for you, including city names.</string>

    <string name="help_friends_title">Friends System</string>
    <string name="help_friends_desc">You can share your trips and experiences with friends by sending a share file. Imported experiences from your friends appear in a separate feed. The best part: Were you on a trip together? With the plus icon at the top right, you can directly copy a shared trip or experience into your own feed.</string>

    <string name="help_calendar_title">Calendar View</string>
    <string name="help_calendar_desc">In the calendar view, you have the perfect temporal overview. Days on which you had experiences or were traveling are marked. This way, you can quickly find out what you did on a specific day last year.</string>

    <string name="help_stats_title">Statistics</string>
    <string name="help_stats_desc">How many kilometers did you travel this year? How many countries have you already visited? The statistics view evaluates your trips and experiences and shows you exciting facts about your travel behavior.</string>

    <string name="help_bucket_title">Bucket List</string>
    <string name="help_bucket_desc">Plan your dreams! In the bucket list, you can save places you absolutely want to visit. As soon as you set a date for an entry, it is automatically added to your feed as a planned experience.</string>

    <string name="help_auto_detect_title">Automatic Detection</string>
    <string name="help_auto_detect_desc">The app can regularly scan your gallery in the background for new images. If you take photos that are more than X kilometers away from your home location, PlacesTracker automatically suggests creating a new experience from them.</string>

    <string name="help_backup_title">Backup System</string>
    <string name="help_backup_desc">Safety first! Using the backup system, you can export your entire database, including all links, into a file. This way, you can easily take your data with you when changing devices or back it up regularly.</string>

    <string name="help_personalize_title">Personalization &amp; Timeline</string>
    <string name="help_personalize_desc">Choose your own theme and language. The timeline gallery also scans your entire local photo collection, showing each image at its capture location on the interactive 3D globe, letting you travel visually through your past.</string>

    <string name="help_donate_title">Support Development</string>
    <string name="help_donate_desc">PlacesTracker is a passion project and completely ad-free. If you like the app, feel free to support its further development with a small donation. Thank you!</string>
    <string name="btn_donate_kofi">Support on Ko-fi</string>

    <string name="visions">Visions</string>
    <string name="visions_desc">What the app should still learn</string>
    <string name="vision_item_1">Like and comment on trips</string>
